transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hi, I was just calling to see if I could cancel my prescription.

Speaker 1: Sure, I can help you out with that. Give me one second to pull up your profile.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Alright, Augustine, can you just confirm your date of birth?

Speaker 2: Yes, it's 12-13-85.

Speaker 1: Thank you so much. I see you're a VIP status customer.

Speaker 2: Oh, I see the doctor put you on refills on a monthly basis, which you do not have to have.

Speaker 1: How's the medication working out for you?

Speaker 2: It doesn't really work for me.

Speaker 1: Yeah, that's what I'm asking.

Speaker 2: Because it looks like here I can see from the pharmacy's notes you did not receive the AGB.

Speaker 1: They sent you just the regular generic Viagra.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Give me a second. I'm going to get you out of replacement,

Speaker 2: and then I'm going to tell you how you can confirm you received the correct medication.

Speaker 1: And I'm going to send you 100 milligrams instead of 50s.

Speaker 2: Give me one second.

Speaker 1: 100 milligrams.

Speaker 2: I'm sending you 25.

Speaker 1: Okay. Alright, perfect. So that went through.

Speaker 2: I'm sending you a quantity of 2,500 milligrams instead of 50s.

Speaker 1: So when you get this new bottle, on the bottle it's going to say AGB,

Speaker 2: but it's also going to say Greenstone.

Speaker 1: Greenstone is the name of Pfizer's manufacturer in France.

Speaker 2: And then on the pill, the only number imprinted is going to be the number 100 for the milligrams.

Speaker 1: Because right now imprinted on your pills is going to be the letters AC,

Speaker 2: I think 390 or 340 or something like that.

Speaker 1: And your bottle will say APCO.

Speaker 2: So that's just generic.

Speaker 1: So I'm sending you out the correct medication.

Speaker 2: And then I'm going to go ahead and pause your refills for six months.

Speaker 1: I'm going to pause it until July 31st of 2026.

Speaker 2: And then I'll give you my extension so you can let me know how the AGB works out for you.

Speaker 1: Okay, sounds good.

Speaker 2: Okay, perfect. Do you have a pen?

Speaker 1: Give me a second.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: 0020.

Speaker 1: And my name is Michelle.

Speaker 2: No problem. Take your time.

Speaker 1: 0020 and my name is Michelle.

Speaker 2: Michelle.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 1: Yeah, not a problem. Have a great day, Augustine.

Speaker 2: All right, you too. Thank you.

Speaker 1: Thanks. Bye.
